By Daniel Dada Three students of Government Secondary School (GSS), Wuse Zone 3, Government Secondary School (GSS), Apo Resettlement and Government Secondary School (GSS), Wuye have each been given the Tongston Entrepreneurship Holdings and Skills Outside School Foundation one year scholarship. A statement jointly signed by the Assistant Manager, Tongston Media, Fatima Aliu and Media and Communications Officer, Skills Outside School Foundation, Benny Atsua, said the three competing secondary schools were hosted on Kaftan TV in a game show, with three senior secondary girls represented from each school. “After a competitive round of presentations, a decision was made by the judges which announced Government Secondary School Wuse Zone 3 as winner, followed by Government Secondary School Apo Resettlement as the first runner up and Government Secondary School Wuye as second runner up,” the statement reads in part. The CEO of Tongston Entrepreneurship Holding, Engr. Bello Tongo, commended the uniqueness of the projects presented by the young girls.